organizing dataset

Kline_report <- read_sav("Kline_complete_2.sav") %>% 
  replace_with_na_all( condition = ~.x == 999)

neg.bprs <- c("BPRS1.03", "BPRS1.13", "BPRS1.16", "BPRS1.17")
pos.bprs <- c("BPRS1.05", "BPRS1.09") 

DEP.BPRS <- Kline_report %>% # nb = negative BPRS - data set
  select(neg.bprs, pos.bprs) 

NB <- DEP.BPRS %>% select(neg.bprs)

calculating f-scores

2nd PCA - BPRS - dep symp - F-scores

DB <- Kline_report %>% #DB = depressive BPRS  
  select(pos.bprs) %>% 
  bind_cols(as_tibble(pca.nb$scores)) %>% 
  rename(neg.factor = PC1)

#PCA anlaysis
pca.db <- pca(DB, nfactors = 1, rotate = "varimax")

New idea

Why not run a PCA for with a single component? Or even a PCA with two components? (see below)
